title: What's Vegetarian and What's Not in Thailand
tags: food Thai|Thailand|Chiang Mai|food court|street food|markets|vegetarian food in Thailand|figuring out w/hat foods are vegetarian in Thailand|tour through a loal food market in Chiang Mai|vegetarian food
description:
To read the entire story about traveling as a vegetarian in Thailand, go to https://holeinthedonut.com/2014/02/18/traveling-as-a-vegetarian-in-thailand/, and if you enjoyed this video, please consider subscribing to my YouTube channel.

Because I'm a vegetarian, finding food can sometimes be stressful as I travel the world perpetually. I planned to spend two months in Thailand last year, and since I'd been there many times I was aware that many vegetarians options were available. My problem was the language barrier; I speak a little Thai but not enough to ask about all the food choices at street food stalls, markets, or food courts. So I asked a Thai friend to accompany me to the local food bazaar in the lower level of Central Airport Plaza in Chiang Mai to show me the ropes. Her explanation and descriptions gave me confidence to eat with the locals and take advantage of the much lower prices, rather than in the pricier restaurants that cater to tourists.

title: Anantara Riverside Resort & Spa Bangkok - Bangkok hotels and resorts - Bangkok holiday
tags: Anantara Riverside Resort and Spa|Anantara Riverside Hotel|Bangkok Resorts|Bangkok (City/Town/Village)|Riverside Hotels|Chao Phraya River (Body Of Water)|Saphan Taksin BTS Station (Location)|Thailand|Hotel (Industry)|River view deluxe room|TripAdvisor (Website)|Travel|Resort (Project)|Canon PowerShot (Product Line)|Tourism (Industry)|Hotels in Bangkok|Hotel chains in Bangkok|Tourism (Interest)|Resort (Industry)|Hotel (Accommodation Type)
description:
Watch all our THAILAND TRAVEL VIDEOS, Link in comments section below. This is a view from our river and pool view balcony (deluxe room) at the Anantara Riverside Resort and Spa in Bangkok. The view of the Chao Phraya River, the hotels swimming pool, canal system and the well maintained garden is fantastic. The balcony is however very small, could hardly fit two chairs and a table. When we where there in December the sun never shined on the balcony. 

We had chosen this hotel for its lovely garden and swimming pool (we wanted to have an oasis to retreat to after a long day in the busy and hectic Bangkok city). We unfortunately found that although the hotel is fantastic and offers a free shuttle boat service between the hotel and Saphan Taksin BTS Station it was a little far away from the city center making travel time rather inconvenient. Other people have said the same on Tripadvisor (long travel times between the hotel and city) and now having stayed there my wife and I must agree. We would definitely recommend this hotel to others but would be sure to make them aware that much of there Bangkok sightseeing time will be wasted on travel time and waiting time for the BTS Sky train and hotel shuttle boat.

The Anantara Bangkok Riverside Resort & Spa describes itself, "Situated on 11 riverside acres of verdant gardens, Anantara Bangkok Riverside Resort & Spa seamlessly blends the thrill of urban living with the serene charms of tropical luxury. Imparted with Thai tradition and legendary Anantara service, this exotic Bangkok resort offers a respite from the hustle and bustle of the busy metropolis.Take in the sunset from the edge of the pier, watching as river life unfolds before your eyes. Indulge in pampering spa treatments set in the tranquil environment of your own private garden. Enjoy unforgettable meals at any of our 10 bars or restaurants, each offering individual delicacies. Discover a new entertainment and lifestyle complex at Asiatique nightmarket, Bangkok‚Äô s latest landmark for shopping and nightlife.  Embrace the unique harmony of luxury and nature within this stunning Bangkok resort & spa..."

This video is filmed with a Canon Powershot SX210 IS Camera.

title: T&K Seafood in Bangkok Chinatown - Street food seafood - Bangkok restaurants
tags: T & K Seafood|Seafood restaurants in Bangkok|Seafood restaurants in Thailand|Seafood (Cuisine)|Thailand (Country)|Bangkok (City/Town/Village)|Yaowarat Road (Road)|Phadung Dao|Chinatown (Neighborhood)|R&L Seafood|Lek and Rut Seafood|Restaurant (Industry)|Canon PowerShot (Product Line)|Bangkok Street food|Chinatown street food|Cheap seafood|Food
description:
Watch all our THAILAND TRAVEL VIDEOS, Link in comments section below. T and K Seafood located in Chinatown Bangkok is a must visit street restaurant for any seafood lover. The T&K Seafood restaurant offers a large and reasonably priced selection of delicious seafood dishes, noodles and fried rice. Obviously as the name implies the specialty of the restaurant is seafood and seafood lovers will not be disappointed.

The menu includes prawn, crab, mussels, oysters, fish (White Snapper), clams, calamari, snails, crab eggs, lobster, crayfish etc. The restaurant is extremely popular with tourists and locals so try to come early in the evening so that you don't have to wait for a table. The line is long on the street however the waiting process is organised with a cue number allocated to everybody. My wife and I where very pleased to find this restaurant which we found thanks to Phil in Bangkok, and expat living in Bangkok who has made loads of videos with tips and information about Bangkok. Thanks Phil we enjoyed your videos! )
The T and K Seafood Restaurant is Bangkok street food at its best located in Chinatown on the corner of Yaowarat and Phadung Dao (Roads).

Tip: Just opposite T & K Seafood is R & L Seafood (Lek and Rut Seafood). Both of these Chinatown seafood restaurants are good, equally busy and equally popular, although we did find that the R & L restaurant was most efficient. The staff at the T&K Seafood restaurant wear Green T-shirts and the staff at the R&L Seafood restaurant wear red T-shirts.

This video is filmed with a Canon Powershot SX210 IS Camera.

Cabin view of take off of our domestic flight from Phuket International Airport to Bangkok International Airport commonly known as Suvarnabhumi Airport (HKT to BKK). 

The flight was on board one of Thai Airway¬¥s newly renovated Boeing 747-400 Jumbo jets in economy class. title: TAKEOFF - Thai Airways Boeing 747-400 takeoff from Suvarnabhumi Airport - Cabin view

description:
Watch our TRIP REPORTS, Link in comments section below.
Cabin view of taxiing and takeoff of a Thai Airways Boeing 747 Jumbo Jet. The aircraft was flying from Bangkok, Thailand (Suvarnabhumi Airport) to Copenhagen, Denmark (Copenhagen, Kastrup Airport). Our seats were located in Economy Class and unfortunately Economy class had still not been renovated with new seats and personal in-flight entertainment systems. This was supposed to have been done in connection with Thai Airways celebrating its 40th anniversary of flights to Copenhagen. Unfortunately the cabin renovation was delayed on this route or aircraft type. Flight from BKK to CPH. This takeoff footage is filmed from an onboard perspective.

Wiki writes about Thai Airways, "Thai Airways International Public Company Limited, also trading as THAI (SET: THAI, Thai: ‡∏ö‡∏£‡∏¥‡∏©‡∏±‡∏ó ‡∏Å‡∏≤‡∏£‡∏ö‡∏¥‡∏ô‡πÑ‡∏ó‡∏¢ ‡∏à‡∏≥‡∏Å‡∏±‡∏î (‡∏°‡∏´‡∏≤‡∏ä‡∏ô)) is the flag carrier airline of Thailand. Formed in 1988, the airline has its corporate headquarters in Vibhavadi Rangsit Road, Chatuchak District, Bangkok, and primarily operates out of Suvarnabhumi Airport. THAI is a founding member of the Star Alliance..."

Wiki writes about the Boeing 747 Jumbo passenger aircraft, "The Boeing 747 is a wide-body commercial airliner and cargo transport aircraft, often referred to by its original nickname, Jumbo Jet, or Queen of the Skies. Its iconic "hump" upper deck along the forward part of the aircraft make it among the world's most recognizable aircraft and was the first wide-body produced. Manufactured by Boeing's Commercial Airplane unit in the United States, the original version of the 747 had two and a half times greater capacity than the Boeing 707, one of the common large commercial aircraft of the 1960s..."

Wiki writes about Bangkok Airport, "Suvarnabhumi Airport, also known as Bangkok International Airport, is one of two international airports serving Bangkok, Thailand. The other is Don Mueang International Airport..."

title: Elephant Nature Park in Mae Taeng, Thailand
tags: Thailand|Chiang Mai|Mae Taeng|elephant nature park|elephants|rescue|charity|proper treatment of elephants in Thailand|rescuing elephants in Thailand|humane treatment of elephants in Thailand|should I ride an elephant|elephant rescue park in northern Thailand
description:
To read the entire story about my visit to the Elephant Nature Park in Mae Taeng, Thailand, go to https://holeinthedonut.com/2014/02/08/elephant-rescue-in-thailand/, and if you enjoyed this video, please consider subscribing to my YouTube channel.

In the hills an hour north of Chiang Mai, Thailand, elephants rescued from circuses, logging operations, and street begging are cared for at Elephant Nature Park. Unlike other "elephant camps" in the area, they are not used for entertainment. Guests do not ride the elephants, nor are the mahouts permitted to use bull hooks to train them. 

The park is the inspiration and passion of Lek Chailert, a diminutive woman who fell in love with elephants at the age of 16, when she trekked with missionaries into the jungle and saw a bull elephant with deep gashes in his chest from ropes used to drag logs out of the forest. He was screaming in pain and angry, and Lek knew she had to do something. As soon as she saved enough money, she returned with medicine and before long villagers and mahouts were telling her about other elephants that were suffering. Eventually she was able to purchase acreage and build the camp that now cares for 37 elephants, 7 of whom are totally blind from abuse, as well as a plethora or other abandoned or abused animals, including dogs, cats, goats, cows, buffalo, and more.

Visitors to the park spend the day learning about elephants, feeding them, and bathing them in the river. The park has an office in Chiang Mai that arranges for day trips, which include pick up from local hotels as well as van transportation there and back.

title: Cheeky Birds in Thailand - Indian Myna Acridotheres tristis Koh Samui
tags: Indian Myna|Acridotheres tristis|Birds of Asia|Chaweng Beach|Koh Samui|Thailand|Chaweng Regent Beach Resort|Common Myna (Organism Classification)|Ko Samui (Island)|Bird (Organism Classification)|Bird|Canon PowerShot (Product Line)|Brown and yellow bird|talking birds|singing birds|funny birds|Ko Samui (Geographical Feature)|Acridotheres (Organism Classification)|Common Myna (Animal)
description:
An Indian Minor sings and performs on the balcony in Koh Samui Thailand. The balcony is at the Chaweng Regent Beach Resort in Koh Samui. The Indian Minor is also knowen as the Common Minor and its Latin name is Acridotheres tristis. According to Wikipedia the Common Myna or Indian Myna is a member of the Sturnidae family (starlings and Mynas). The Myna species are native to the Asian continent but have been introduced to the USA, Canada, Pacific Islands, Australia, Africa and Indian Ocean islands.

Wiki writes about the Common Myna,  "The common myna (Acridotheres tristis), sometimes spelled mynah, also sometimes known as "Indian myna", is a member of the family Sturnidae (starlings and mynas) native to Asia. An omnivorous open woodland bird with a strong territorial instinct, the myna has adapted extremely well to urban environments. The common myna is an important motif in Indian culture and appears both in Sanskrit and Prakrit literature. Myna is derived from the Hindi language mainƒÅ which itself is derived from Sanskrit madanƒÅ..."

title: The Citadel and Forbidden Purple City-Hue, Vietnam (With Historical Facts)
tags: The Citadel|Forbidden Purple City|Purple Forbidden City|Battle of Hue|Hue Vietnam|Tet Offensive|Vietnam War|American War|Imperial Capital of Vietnam|Hue|Ngo Mon Gate|Emperor Minh Mang|Thai Hoa Palace|Palace of Supreme Harmony|Trung Dao Bridge|Dien Tho Palace|Mieu Temple|Nguyen Dynasty|Dynastic Urns|Hien Lam Pavillion
description:
I took a fascinating tour of an area rich in Vietnamese and American history. My guide Thanh had personally witnessed hand-to-hand combat here as a 12 year-old during the Vietnam War. Hue was the imperial capital of Vietnam from 1802-1945 and the Forbidden Purple City contained the residence of the Emperor and Royal Family. Like the Forbidden City in Beijing, only royalty and invited guests could come here. The Citadel is a walled fortress and palace that was built in the early 1800's. During the 1968 Tet Offensive and the Battle of Hue, thousands of Vietnamese and hundreds of Americans were killed during fighting here.

title: Dong Ba Market-My Favorite Food Market in Vietnam
tags: Dong Ba Market|Dong Ba|Hue|Hue Vietnam|Vietnamese food markets|Dong Ba food market|hue food market
description:
I received a private tour (with my excellent guide Thanh) of Dong Ba Market in Hue, Vietnam, which was my favorite Vietnamese food market. The local food market is the heart and soul of every Vietnamese city and town and Dong Ba Market is no exception. It's the largest food market in Central Vietnam and like most Vietnamese food markets, about 90% of the vendors are women. Thousands of people come here every day and this market is full of hustle and bustle-anything you need is here!

title: Thien Mu Pagoda-Hue, Vietnam (With Historical Facts)
tags: Thien Mu Pagoda|Thien Mu|Heavenly Lady Pagoda|Hue|Hue Vietnam|Vietnam|Lord Nguyen Huong|vietnamese pagoda|seven story pagoda|tower of superior buddhist monk
description:
Thien Mu Pagoda, or "Heavenly Lady" pagoda, is the unofficial symbol of Hue when it was the former Imperial capital of Vietnam. The pagoda is seven stories, the tallest in Vietnam, and was erected in the mid 19th Century. Also on the grounds is "A Tower of the Superior Buddhist Monk," the burial grounds for a former head of the pagoda.

title: Emperor Tu Duc Tombs-Hue, Vietnam (With Historical Facts)
tags: Emperor Tu Duc Tombs|Emperor Tu Duc|Nguyen Dynasty (Family)|Hue|Hue vietnam|tombs in vietnam|Tu Duc Tombs|Tu Duc summer house|Tu Duc
description:
Emperor Tu Duc was the fourth emperor of Vietnam's Nguyen Dynasty. He reigned from 1847-1883. On the grounds you can find his tomb and summer house. The Emperor was known for shutting off Vietnam from the rest of the world and for refusing to modernize the country. According to legend, he cursed the French with his dying breath in 1883.

title: Tiger Arena: Tigers and Elephants Fought to the Death-Hue, Vietnam
tags: Tiger Arena|Ho Quyen|Tiger Arena Hue|Hue|Hue Vietnam|Emperor Minh Mang|tigers|elephants|fight to the death|tigers and elephants fight to the death|tigers and elephants deathmatch|Tigers Arena|Vietnam|vietnam colisseum
description:
This is Vietnam's Roman Colosseum. Tiger Arena (Ho Quyen) was built in 1830 during the reign of Emperor Minh Mang to serve as an entertainment venue for the royalty and public. Tigers (who represented goodness) and elephants (who represented goodness) would fight to the death and the elephant would always win because the tigers would be starved and their teeth and claws were removed. The last battle took place here in 1904.

title: 1,000 Year-Old Sculptures-Cham Museum (Museum of Cham Sculpture)-Danang, Vietnam
tags: Cham Museum|Museum of Cham Sculpture|danang|Da Nang|Cham Museum danang|Cham|Champa|Kingdom of Champa|Cham sculptures|Shiva|Manu|terra cotta|Brahma|hindu altars|buddhist altars
description:
The Cham Museum (or Museum of Cham Sculpture) in Danang, Vietnam, contains the largest collection of Cham sculptures and artwork in the world. Many of the artifacts are over 1,000 years old. The Kingdom of Champa controlled parts of Vietnam for hundreds of years and dissolved in the early 19th Century.

title: Sulamani Temple Bagan Myanmar (Burma)
description:
There are so much to learn from Buddhist culture and the way of life, this culture is changing very fast indeed. 
I hope we all aim to protect and care for each other. 

The Sulamani Temple is a Buddhist temple located in the village of Minnanthu in Burma. 

The temple is one of the most-frequently visited in Bagan. 

It was built in 1183 by King Narapati sithu, and is similar to the Thatbyinnyu Temple in design.

title: Reunification Palace Private Tour-Saigon (Ho Chi Minh City), Vietnam
tags: Reunification Palace|Saigon|Ho Chi Minh City|Saigon presidential palace|vietnam|Reunification Palace Saigon|Reunification Palace Tour|Independence Palace|Reunification Hall|Reunification Palace Ho Chi Minh City
description:
The President of South Vietnam lived and worked here until the Fall of Saigon in 1975 when North Vietnamese tanks crashed through the front gates and the president surrendered. The inside seems pretty much untouched since that time. You can see the war planning rooms, receiving rooms, dining rooms, bedrooms, movie theater, kitchen and the secret passageway that goes 2 kilometers underground to the airport. In 1962 two air force pilots bombed the palace instead of bombing the Viet Cong-one wing was destroyed but the president and his family survived the assassination attempt.

tags: Saigon|Ho Chi Minh City|Saigon Vietnam|Vietnam|Saigon attractions|Saigon highlights|Saigon Landmarks|Ho Chi Minh City attractions|Notre Dame Cathedral|Saigon General Post Office|Hotel Continental Saigon|Saigon Opera House|Municipal Theatre Ho Chi Minh City|Saigon Town Hall|Saigon City Hall|Bitexco Financial Tower|Vietnam's tallest buildings
description:
During this private tour of Saigon, Vietnam, now known as Ho Chi Minh City, we see the Notre Dame Cathedral, General Post Office, Hotel Continental, the Opera House, City Hall, and the Bitexco Financial Tower, second tallest building in Vietnam. Saigon is Vietnam's largest city and is the former capital of South Vietnam before the Communists won the Vietnam War.

title: Cu Chi Tunnels Tour-Vietnam
tags: Cu Chi Tunnels|Vietnam|Cu Chi Tunnels Vietnam|Cu Chi Tunnels Tour|Vietnam tunnels|Vietnam War|Viet Cong|booby traps|cu chi tunnels booby traps
description:
During the Cu Chi Tunnels tour, we walked through a tunnel (which has been widened for tourists), saw some of the bunkers and booby traps, and walked by a shooting range where you can fire guns for a small price. Visiting the Cu Chi Tunnels helped me understand why the North Vietnamese and Viet Cong won the Vietnam War. They dug 70 mile long tunnels by hand and hid there during the day despite horrendous conditions. You have to have a certain amount of fortitude to do that.

title: Angkor Wat, Cambodia-World's Largest Religious Monument! (With Historical Facts)
tags: Angkor Wat|Angkor Wat Cambodia|Cambodia Temples|Hindu Temples|Buddhist Temples Cambodia|Hindu Temples Cambodia|Religious Monuments|Famous temples|Khmer Rouge|Siem Reap|UNESCO World Heritage Site|Asparas|King Suryavarman|City of Temples|the Chams|Meru
description:
Angkor Wat is the reason I came to Cambodia. It's the symbol of Cambodia and appears on its national flag. Angkor Wat translates to "Temple City" or "City of Temples" and is 900 years old. The temple was first Hindu, then Buddhist and was built as a miniature replica of the universe. Despite the solemn surroundings, I managed to inject some humor (or at least tried to) into my private tour.

11:28 Main tower and courtyard
11:46 Large wall of bas-reliefs depicting battle
12:21 Reflecting pool
12:37 Back at entrance at sunset
12:56 Woman picking water lilies from reflecting pool

description:
Little Andaman : The fourth largest island of the archipelago / India.
Editer-Jitendra Kumar Jitu
Voice-Anju Paudel
Little Andaman is situated at the southern end of the Andaman & Nicobar Islands opposite the Great Andaman Island. It is the fourth largest island of the archipelago. The Duncan Passage separates Little Andaman from Rutland Bay of Great Andaman.
Little Andaman has an evergreen rain forest which paves way for a very rich biodiversity. There are two waterfalls in the island -- White Surf waterfall which is 6.5 kms from Hut Bay Jetty and the Whisper Wave which is 20 kms from the same. It also involves a 4 km trek through the rain forest. On the way to White Surf waterfalls, elephant safari can be enjoyed. One can also visit the Elephant lumbering sites and the elephant calves training sites. Also, Little Andaman is famous for Red Oil Palm Plantation and has a large area under the plantation regime. Both these places can be visited on the way to White Surf and Butler Bay.

The most famous and beautiful beach on Little Andamans is the Butler Bay Beach. It lies at a distance of 14 kms from the Hut Bay Jetty.
Activities at the island also involve snorkelling, Diving, Swimming, Game Fishing, Coral watching, and Sun Basing etc. Though the Northern side of the beach is a popular surfing site. It is advisable that tourists carry their own surfing equipment if they wish to go surfing in the sea. Butler Bay gives a chance to the bird watchers to catch a glimpse of species like Hawabill and Nicobarese pigeon. Butler Bay is also home to some of the rarest marine turtles. There are beaches like Netaji Nagar and Harminder Bay Beach.

Little Andaman is 210 kms south of Port Blair and takes almost 7 to 9 hours to reach. There are around three boat services a week from the capital city.

title: Walking Around Cambodian Floating Fishing Village-Kompong Khleang
tags: Kompong Khleang|floating fishing village|Cambodian fishing village|Cambodian floating fishing village|Cambodia|houses on stilts|walking in Cambodian village|Cambodian countryside|Buddhist monastery
description:
I went off the beaten path and walked around a fascinating floating fishing village in Kompong Khleang, Cambodia, which included a brief tour of a Buddhist monastery. The village is about 25 miles (40 km) from Siem Reap. The houses are perched on stilts about 33 feet (10 meters) above the ground to prevent flooding during the rainy season and the homes have no electricity. This was a rare glimpse into a way of life that is totally different from what most of us are used to. It was like going back in time.

title: Hauntingly Beautiful Bayon Temple, Angkor Thom (With Historical Facts)
tags: The Bayon|Angkor Thom|Siem Reap|Cambodia|Cambodian temples|stone faces|King Jayavarman VII|bas reliefs|face towers|South Gate of Angkor Thom|Hindu temple|Buddhist temple|smiling stone faces
description:
While many people go to Siem Reap to visit Angkor Wat, no trip would be complete without a visit to The Bayon, which is part of the Angkor Thom temple complex. The complex is almost 1,000 years old and is known for its many gigantic smiling stone faces and for its bas reliefs. It was voted the #1 attraction in Siem Reap on TripAdvisor. My visit here is one I will always remember.

title: Baphuon Temple-Angkor Thom, Siem Reap, Cambodia (With Historical Facts)
tags: The Baphuon|Baphuon|Angkor Thom|Siem Reap|Cambodia|Cambodian temples|The Baphuon angkor thom|Shiva|Hindu temple|Buddhist temple|Udayadityavarman II
description:
The Baphuon is a temple located at Angkor Thom in Siem Reap Cambodia. It was built in the mid 11th Century and was the state temple of Udayadityavarman II. The temple was originally dedicated to the Hindu God Shiva but was converted to a Buddhist temple in the late 15th Century. By the 20th Century, much of the temple had collapsed and reconstruction efforts started around 1950 and were finally completed in 2011. The final stage, over the last 16 years, had seen a 300 person team tackle what had become the largest three-dimensional jigsaw puzzle in the world.

title: GOOD TOUR OF PATTAYA | THAILAND
tags: Pattaya|Pattaya Exhibition And Convention Hall|Pattaya tourist attraction|Best tourist places in World|emerald buddha|river kwai|prasat hin phimai|statue of liberty|trevi fountain|wat yanasangwararam woramahawihan|sri racha tiger zoo|nong nooch tropical botanical garden|pattaya crocodile farm|pattaya parck beach resort water park|walking street|thailand tourism|sex tourism|TOURISM|nearby tourist attractions|environmental tourism|tourism guide|NALANDATV
description:
TOUR OF PATTAYA | THAILAND
A breathtaking beach resort and a serene holiday is a real treat to a soul. Pattaya is among the cities that will soothe the mind and soul. It is 165 km away from the national capital, Bangkok and located off the Gulf of Thailand. Pattaya stands as a favorite destination for retired people to settle down. Not only do the local expatriates prefer this destination but also foreigners. Thailand has a special visa for people aged over 50 which allow them to come and settle in this city. Pattaya is not only a pleasant city to live in but also very affordable for a decent life style. 
Though the official transliteration is still 'Phatthaya', this city is known to the world as 'Pattaya.' 

The name of this city is derived from the name 'Thap Phraya' only to become later as Phattaya. Phattaya means wind blowing from the southwest to the northeast at the beginning of the rainy season. Pttya has always been a small village with fishing as its major occupation. During the Vietnam War American servicemen arrived to this city for relaxation. This arrival for rest transformed this city into a famous beach resort. Over 14.5 million tourists visit Pattaya in a year. Hotels and resorts adorn the beaches of Pattaya now. The Central Festival Pattaya Beach Mall and hotel, Asia's largest beachfront shopping mall, is also situated on Beach Rd in central Pattaya. The Pattaya Bay Area is one of Asia's largest beach resorts and the second most visited city in Thailand, after Bangkok. 

Jomtien Beach is another famous beach which offers some water sports like jet skis, parasailing and small sail boat hire. The islands are divided into Near islands, Far islands and Ko Larn (main land). These names are only for the touristic purpose. These are not shown on any maritime charts published by the government. Many of the islands offer scuba diving activities and also have public beaches. 

Pattaya is popular for activities such as playing golf, diving and scuba diving. Some of the major attractions in this city are Sri Racha Tiger Zoo, Nong Nooch Tropical Botanical Garden, The Million Years Stone Park, Pattaya Crocodile Farm, Pattaya Park Beach Resort Water Park, Funny Land Amusement Park, Siriporn Orchid Farm, Silverlake Winery, Underwater World Pattaya (world-class aquarium), the Thai Alangkarn Theater Pattaya (cultural show), Bottle Art Museum, Ripley's Believe It or Not Museum, and Underwater World, Khao Phra Tamnak or Khao Phra Bat, Sanctuary of Trut, Mini Siam, Temple of the Emerald Buddha, Democracy Monument, Bridge over the River Kwai, Prasat Hin Phimai, Tower Bridge of London, Eiffel Tower, the Statue of Liberty and Trevi Fountain and Wat Yanasangwararam Woramahawihan.

Phare Ponleu Selpak provides free artistic and academic education and social support services to 1,200 at-risk Cambodian youth daily. Phare Circus and Phare Creative Studio provide well-paying job opportunities in Cambodia and overseas. Revenue generated  financially supports the school.

title: The Beaumont Partnership Foundation's flagship project - Ruam Pattana School Chaiyaphum
tags: Thailand|Chaiyaphum|Province|Beaumont Foundation|Charity|Foundation|Education|Free|Quality|High Standard|Innovative|Teaching|Ruam Pattana School|HE James Wise|Australian Ambassador to Thailand|Beaumont Partnership|Design Studio|Architecture|Interior Design|Landscape Design|Tim Beaumont|Pace Developments|Destination Thailand TV|Capital TV Bangkok|Raine Grady|Waikato Invest|The Beaumont Partnership Foundation's flagship project - Ruam Pattana School Chaiyaphum
description:
The Beaumont Foundation was established five years ago to serve needy rural communities and to offer a high standard of education to ordinary children free of charge. It aims to maximize student potential through modern and innovative teaching techniques that will help them become the very best they can be. 
The Foundation's flagship project -- the Ruam Pattana school in Chaiyaphum Province -- has just begun operations with its first student intake. It is an inspiring project that aims to create a better world and a brighter future for less fortunate children.
The school has been designed in a sustainable way that blends into the rural environment. 
The Beaumont Foundation is supported by the Beaumont Partnership, a design studio with a focus on its people and their collective talents and creativity. It is internationally recognised in three core areas of client and industry service - architecture, interior design and landscape design. Having been operating successfully in Thailand for 23 years The Partners established the Foundation as a way of giving back to the country which has supported them, and provided them with so many fulfilling opportunities.
A good education not only transforms the lives of its students but benefits the entire community. Now these children have the opportunity to realize their dreams.....
www.tbp-foundation.com

title: THE MOST FAMOUS VISIST DESTINATION   ANDAMAN & NICOBAR ISLANDS | INDIA
tags: Andman & Nicobar India.|Andman|nicobar|tourism of india|Andaman And Nicobar Islands|Andaman Sea|Union Territory of India.|Port Blair|Malacca|Indian state|The 2004 tsunami|Flora|Fauna|Tourist places|Sister islands|Assam - The land of Natural Beauty.|nalandatv|world best beach goa|blue sea water goa|top destination in India|best sea beaches goa|ISLANDS OF INDIA|BEST VACATION DESTINATION INDIA|best tourist places|tourism near me|popular tourist destinations
description:
ANDAMAN & NICOBAR ISLANDS | INDIA 
Voice-Akanksha Singh.
The Andaman and Nicobar Islands are a group of islands at the juncture of the Bay of Bengal and Andaman Sea, and are a Union Territory of India.
The territory is 150 km (93 mi) north of Aceh in Indonesia and separated from Thailand and Burma by the Andaman Sea. It comprises two island groups, the Andaman Islands and the Nicobar Islands, separated by the 10¬∞ N parallel, with the Andamans to the north of this latitude, and the Nicobars to the south. The Andaman Sea lies to the east and the Bay of Bengal to the west.
The territory's capital is the Andamanese town of Port Blair. The total land area of the territory is approximately 8,073 km2 (3,117 sq mi). The capital of Nicobar Islands is Car Nicobar also known as Malacca.
There are 572 islands in the territory having an area of 7,950 km2 (3,070 sq mi). Of these, about 34 are permanently inhabited. The islands extend from 6¬∞ to 14¬∞ North latitudes and from 92¬∞ to 94¬∞ East longitudes. The Andamans are separated from the Nicobar group by a channel (the Ten Degree Channel) some 150 km (93 mi) wide. The highest point is located in North Andaman Island (Saddle Peak at 732 m (2,402 ft)). The Andaman group has 325 islands which cover an area of 6,170 km2 (2,382 sq mi) while the Nicobar group has only 24 islands with an area of 1,765 km2 (681 sq mi).[12]:33
Flora-
Andaman & Nicobar Islands are blessed with a unique tropical rainforest canopy, made of a mixed flora with elements from Indian, Myanmarese, Malaysian and endemic floral strains. So far, about 2,200 varieties of plants have been recorded, out of which 200 are endemic and 1,300 do not occur in mainland India.
Fauna-
This tropical rain forest despite its isolation from adjacent land masses is surprisingly rich with a diversity of animal life.
About 50 varieties of forest mammals are found to occur in the Andaman and Nicobar Islands. Some are endemic, including the Andaman Wild Boar. Rodents are the largest group with 26 species, followed by 14 species of bat.

More Update-

title: Best Riverfront Villa-style Nature Resort surrounded by Green Mountainous Scenery in Thailand
tags: hotel|resort|hotel in kanchanaburi|hotel in river kwai|riverfront hotel|nature resort|resotel
description:
River Kwai Resotel is a villa-style resort nestled on the banks of the Kwai Noi River in Kanchanaburi. It features air-conditioned rooms with an outdoor pool and a restaurant. Free WiFi is available in the lobby area.

Surrounded by tropical forests and mountains, all rooms offer a balcony, satellite TV and refrigerator. Free tea/coffee making facilities and bottled water is provided. Private bathroom is equipped with shower facility and free toiletries.

Guests can enjoy a relaxing Thai herbal massage or buy a gift from the Resotel Crafts Village. Tours and sightseeing can be arranged by the resort. Laundry services and free parking is available.

Traditional Thai and international cuisine are served at the jungle-styled restaurant. A bar offers beverages including cocktails and beers.

Located on the edge of Saiyok National Park, River Kwai Resotel is within walking distance to Lawa Cave. It is also accessible by a 9-minute boat ride from Phutakian Pier (Resotel Pier) in Kanchanaburi. Guests can rent a bike to explore the surroundings.

Overlooking the lush mountain and the River Kwai, the on-site restaurant serves a selection of authentic Thai dishes, local Mon specialties, and international delights. Club House Bar has a wide range of alcoholic drinks and refreshing beverages.

www.riverkwairesotel.net - a member of SERENATA Hotels & Resorts Group (www.serenatahotels.com)

title: World Awarded Floating Hotel (Floatel) in Kanchanaburi, Thailand that Float since 1976
tags: river kwai|floatel|floating hotel|hotel|resort|kanchanaburi|hotel in kanchanaburi|thailand|floating resort
description:
Set peacefully by Kwai Noi River, River Kwai Jungle Rafts offers ecologically friendly floating accommodations surrounded by tropical greenery. To enhance the peacefulness and uniqueness of the hotel, rooms that float on a wooden raft use oil lamps and candles instead of electricity.

Featuring walls weaved from local bamboo and decorated with wooden furnishings, each traditional-Mon-house style room comes with a mosquito net, a fan and private bathroom including free toiletries. Rooms also have an outdoor deck with a sun lounger and hammock. Free bottled waters are provided.

Guest enjoy jumping in the river right from their rooms. River Kwai Jungle Hotel can assist with planning hikes, boat trips, mountain biking and canoeing down the river. In the evening, the hotel also has live traditional and Mon tribal performances.

Thai and local Mon dishes as well as refreshing drinks are served at Jungle Restaurant.

Located in the heart of Sai Yok National Park, River Kwai Resort is just 20 minutes‚Äô from the Phutakian Pier (Resotel Pier) by long-tail boat.

www.riverkwaijunglerafts.com - a member of SERENATA Hotels & Resorts Group (www.serenatahotels.com)

title: Beautiful Riverside Tented Camp Hotel Near HellFire Pass Museum & Trail in Kanchanaburi, Thailand
description:
This unique, nature retreat overlooks the historic River Kwai and Hintok Mountain. Nestled in a Hellfire Pass clearing, Hintok River Camp offers accommodations in luxurious canvas tents with free WiFi. It features a natural spring-water pool and daily campfires.

Tents at Camp Hintok River are spacious and furnished with luxurious wooden furniture. All rooms have private bathrooms including a hot shower, a hair dryer and free toiletries. They also feature outdoor showers with hot water, in-room air-conditioning and private verandas. Complimentary bottled waters are provided.

The restaurant and bar is set among tropical trees. It is open for breakfast, lunch and dinner and serves a varied menu, while barbecue is arranged every evening. Guests can relax with Thai massage services or unwind at the lounging area overlooking the river.

www.hintokrivercamp.com - a member of SERENATA Hotels & Resorts Group (www.serenatahotels.com)

description:
She's known as the Queen of Burlesque 
Born as Heather Renee Sweet from Michagan in the United States, Dita Von Teese became her name when her dancing and seductive stripping career took off and she began performing burlesque in 1992.
The glamorous performer was in Thailand for a special event organized by Cointreau -- a brand she represents world wide and some of Thailand's most famous faces in terms of fashion and beauty were on hand at the Peninsula Hotel to see her Cointreau-Versial Show. Here are the parts we can let you see!
For more information visit: www.dita.net

title: A Burmese Journey - One woman's return to Myanmar after 44 years - 8MFH EP9
description:
'The Cinematic Documentary of when Irma El-haj returned to Burma after almost half a century'

'44 Years from Kamayut' is a special episode of '8 miles from home'. Documenting the journey of Jmayel's mother 'Irma El-haj' as she returns to her home town & country of birth; Kamayut township in Yangon, Burma. 

Having left Myanmar 44 years ago during a time of conflict and not returning since, the trip was long overdue. 

She embarked on this journey to rediscover the home she had stored in memories from almost half a century ago. Memories of a good childhood with her mother & father growing up in '3rd street' in Kamayut. Losing her Ruby ring as a teenager in the pond near to her home, and a vivid picture of the local boy 'Bpoun Saa' that used to eat breakfast at her home completely naked.

During her stay with 2 local families in Yangon, she met Cho Cho, Tin Tin and their relatives whom are contacts of friends she knows in the UK. They welcomed Irma with the greatest hospitality and showed her the Yangon that it is today. She then met with Lydia, a young girl from Bethel who showed her the way to her home street in Kamayut.

After 4 days in Yangon, Irma ventured north to see the parts of the country she had never seen before. Namely the ancient temples of Bagan. Watching the sunsets with Badru, Jmayel & Sacha El-haj, they all had time to reflect on the amazing journey they had experienced together as a family...

This cinematic account of Irmas return to Burma is dedicated to Doris Grace Hannay. Irmas mother, who can be seen briefly in '8 miles from home episode 1'. Physically unable to make the journey herself, this movie will allow her to see the world she left behind so many years ago.

For collaborations and business inquiries, please contact via Channel Pages: http://ChannelPages.com/8milesfromhome

title: King Cobra Ready To Attack at a Snake Farm in Bangkok, Thailand
tags: king cobra|snakes|thailand|snake farm|king cobra attack|snake attack|bangkok|bangkok tourist|snake venom|snake anti-venom|snake farms|scary snakes|snake ready to attack
description:
Watch as this King Cobra snake stands ready to attack at the Bangkok Snake Farm. This venomous snake is bred here in order to extract venom for anti-venom production. Read more here: https://www.renegadetravels.com/bangkok-snake-farm-at-queen-saovabha-memorial-institute/


Watch the snake handler pick up the king cobra and get bit! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NIRlQULwRiw


--------------------------------------------------



The Bangkok Snake Farm is a working snake farm where they breed snakes in order to extract venom for anti-venom production. There are over 200 species of snakes in Thailand, over 60 of which are venomous, so it‚Äôs essential for all hospitals to have anti-venom available.



As well as being very educational, the snake farm is also lots of fun. But you will need to plan your day if you want to see both the venom extraction show and the snake handling show, because one is in the morning and the other in the afternoon. But you‚Äôre allowed to leave the farm and use the same ticket to come back later the same day

The Tonle Sap is, together with the largest lake in East Asia, 250 km long, but  a natural phenomenon: In the monsoon season, the Mekong floods and can not absorb any more water, so goes the Tonle Sap back north and thus increases the lake in Siem Reap many times over. Ankor Tom and Angkor Wat and the Bayon Temple and Taprom - - (the well known Temples, where the temples of the Angkor, the period  as Khmer Empire was the largest in East Asia.
Phnom Penh was only during the colonial period (after 1860) King City, the palace complex and the Silver Pagoda dates from this time. Today's capital is situated on the west side of Tonle Sap and the Mekong. The Mekong River is about 2 km wide.

title: MYANMAR's LEBENSADER, der Fluss IRRAWADDY - vom Himalaja in die Andamanensee
description:
Der IRRAWADDY  flie√üt in Burma von Norden (Himalaya) nach S√ºden (Andamanensee)  Indischer Ozean.:  er ist einer der gro√üen Str√∂me Ostasiens (etwas k√ºrzer, Wasserreicher in der Monsunzeit, mit einem wesentlich gr√∂√üerem Delta, als die Donau in Europa).-
Er in seinem Mittellauf umflie√üt er in gro√üem Bogen vor Sagaing und Mandalay das Hochplateau der Shan (Inlesee) um bei Bagan wieder  in gro√üen M√§andern nach S√ºden zu flie√üen.
Wenig n√∂rdlich von Bagan hat er einen einzigen gr√∂√üeren Zufluss - den Chindwin - der das n√∂rdliche Arakangebirge entw√§ssert. (Grenzgebirge zum Golf von Bengalen).-
Der Irrawaddy ist die Lebensader von Burma: 
Verkehrsweg (Stra√üen und Bahnverbindungen sind desolat) und sorgt f√ºr riesige Anbaugebiete von Reis und den meisten Feldfr√ºchten bis zu Erdn√ºssen. 
Vom Mittelalter bis heute sind die bedeutenden Kulturst√§dte an diesem Fluss gewachsen. 
Die Kulturstadt BAGO an der Andamanensee - ehemalige Hauptstadt des MONVOLKES -  liegt bereits au√üerhalb des Deltas des Irrawaddy im SO des Landes.
In seiner Bl√ºtezeit lag es an einem M√ºndungsarm des SALWEENFLUSSES (Nr. 9 in Asien, ein riesiger Fluss, welcher aber nur zu einem 1/4 Teil durch Burma flie√üt).

The only way to truly understand what takes place during a sacred tattoo is to experience it personally, so I made my way through Bangkok's streets to meet Ajarn Rung, a former monk who now devotes his time to helping people's luck turn and their wishes to come true.

Sak Yant Oil Tattoo
Ajarn Rung

title: Phimai Thailand - The old outpost of the Khmer Empire
tags: Thailand|Isan|Issan|Phimai|Khmer|Khmer Empire|Korat Province|Phimai Historical Park|Ancient|Sai|Banyan|Tree|Giant|Phanomrungpuri Hotel|Buriram|Capital TV Bangkok|Dave Kendall|Phimai Thailand|Issan Thailand|History|Travel|Thailand Travel|Travel VLOG|Thailand VLOG|Things to do in Thailand|travel thailand|thailand travel guide|travel tips|Phimai Thailand - The old outpost of the Khmer Empire|Nakhon Ratchasima|Korat|Tourism|Thailand Tourism|north east thailand
description: The town of Phimai in Korat province in Northeastern Thailand, has been continuously settled for over a thousand years. We explore Phimai Historical Park, the Northern outpost of the old Khmer Empire and home to the largest sandstone sanctuary in Thailand. We also encounter a natural wonder of the world -- a giant, 350 year-old Banyan tree at Sai Ngam.

title: Bamboo Train of Battambang, Cambodia
tags: travel|culture|cultural travel|Bamboo Train|Cambodia|Battambang|Khmer|Bamboo Train of Battambang|Riding the Bamboo Train in Battambang Cambodia|Khmer Rouge|handcars on old railroad tracks in Cambodia
description:
To read the entire story about the Bamboo Train of Battambang, Cambodia, go to https://holeinthedonut.com/2012/08/30/bamboo-train-battambang-cambodia/, and if you enjoyed this video, please consider subscribing to my YouTube channel.

After the Khmer Rouge were overthrown in 1979, Cambodians needed a way to move people and goods around the country. Trains no longer ran but the track were still in place, so with typical Cambodian ingenuity, they salvaged old train car wheels and built iron frames, upon which they laid a platform of bamboo. Initially, the platforms were moved along the tracks using wooden paddles but eventually small motors were installed. When the country reopened, tourists flocked in and discovered this curious means of transport, which they named the Bamboo Train. Today, visitors can ride the Bamboo Train on a small portion of the line near Battambang, Cambodia, but its days may be numbered. With the help of China, a new railway is being built across the country. Once the new railroad is complete, the Bamboo Train may still operate in between actual trains, but with wider tracks and a cleared right-of-way, it ill never again be the same.

title: Grand Riverview Hotel Kota Bharu Malaysia
description: https://www.sipandstay.wine/international/malaysia/ This is a luxury style hotel in Malaysia that is about $90 USD per night.  A nice break from guesthouses and hostels while traveling through the country.  Kota Bharu is one of the most conservative towns in the country and is on the border of Thailand.  The night market in town has some of the best street food selection around with an astounding amount of Rats that come out to graze upon what they can find on the ground.  There is no alcohol served at the hotel so we ordered a "mocktail"  while at the pool.  My wife was wearing a Bikini which made the young waiter very nervous.

description: The town of Phimai in Korat province in Northeastern Thailand, has been continuously settled for over a thousand years. We explore Phimai Historical Park, the Northern outpost of the old Khmer Empire and home to the largest sandstone sanctuary in Thailand. We also encounter a natural wonder of the world -- a giant, 350 year-old Banyan tree at Sai Ngam.

title: Bamboo Train of Battambang, Cambodia
tags: travel|culture|cultural travel|Bamboo Train|Cambodia|Battambang|Khmer|Bamboo Train of Battambang|Riding the Bamboo Train in Battambang Cambodia|Khmer Rouge|handcars on old railroad tracks in Cambodia
description:
To read the entire story about the Bamboo Train of Battambang, Cambodia, go to https://holeinthedonut.com/2012/08/30/bamboo-train-battambang-cambodia/, and if you enjoyed this video, please consider subscribing to my YouTube channel.

After the Khmer Rouge were overthrown in 1979, Cambodians needed a way to move people and goods around the country. Trains no longer ran but the track were still in place, so with typical Cambodian ingenuity, they salvaged old train car wheels and built iron frames, upon which they laid a platform of bamboo. Initially, the platforms were moved along the tracks using wooden paddles but eventually small motors were installed. When the country reopened, tourists flocked in and discovered this curious means of transport, which they named the Bamboo Train. Today, visitors can ride the Bamboo Train on a small portion of the line near Battambang, Cambodia, but its days may be numbered. With the help of China, a new railway is being built across the country. Once the new railroad is complete, the Bamboo Train may still operate in between actual trains, but with wider tracks and a cleared right-of-way, it ill never again be the same.

title: Grand Riverview Hotel Kota Bharu Malaysia
description: https://www.sipandstay.wine/international/malaysia/ This is a luxury style hotel in Malaysia that is about $90 USD per night.  A nice break from guesthouses and hostels while traveling through the country.  Kota Bharu is one of the most conservative towns in the country and is on the border of Thailand.  The night market in town has some of the best street food selection around with an astounding amount of Rats that come out to graze upon what they can find on the ground.  There is no alcohol served at the hotel so we ordered a "mocktail"  while at the pool.  My wife was wearing a Bikini which made the young waiter very nervous.

title: Baan Dam - The 'Black House' of Chiang Rai Thailand
tags: Thailand|Chiang Rai|Baan Dam|Black House|Skeletons|Thawan Duchanee|Capital TV Bangkok|Doi-tibet Dachanee|Art|Artist|Tourism|Discover|Attraction|Chiang Rai Thailand|Ban Dam Chiang Rai|Design|Architecture|Travel|Travel VLOG|VLOG|Thailand VLOG|Thailand travel VLOG|Destination Thailand|travel thailand|thailand travel guide|northern thailand|amazing thailand|things to do in chiang rai|thailand travel tips|Baan Dam - The 'Black House' of Chiang Rai Thailand
description:
We are invited in to the eerie Chiang Rai home of national artist Thawan Duchanee. Every corner of the Black House had new surprises. A work-in- progress of more than 35 years, his estate is an interesting collection of over 40 bizarre, surreal structures including a zoo's worth of animal skeletons.

The 'Black House' of Chiang Rai - Baan Dam Thailand

title: SARINGAN AIR NAZAVA:  AIR MINUM SEHAT DAN MURAH

description:
Liputan dari TV Aceh mengenai Saringan air Nazava (https://www.nazava.com). Saringan air ini memurnikan air PAM, air SUMUR dan air hujan supaya menjadi layak untuk diminum. Terdiri di Aceh, Nazava sudah menjual filter air di 50 tempat di Indonesia dan telah mengekspor ke puluhan negara. Dengan saringan air Nazava anda bisa melindungi keluarga dari penyakit. Kualitas air hasil penyaringan air  Nazava lebih terjamin dari air Isi Ulang.  Walaupun kualitas tinggi dan menggunakan teknologi Belanda, produk pemurni air Nazava tidak mahal. Rp230.000,-  sudah cukup untuk membeli filter air Nazava!

tags: jungle flight|chiang mai|thailand|07.11.2011|vilin video produktie|peter van der linden|www.vilin.nl|zipline|adventure|jungle|forest|north thailand|2011|youtube|vilinstudios|vilintravel|fun|high
description:
07.11.2011 - Chiang Mai - Thailand -  Jungle Flight - Treetop Eco-Advetures... is Chiang Mai's Newest and Best attraction! Located atop one of Thailand's 5 highest mountains... you will soar through the jungle on the adventure of a lifetime as you fly over 6km of the Longest.. Highest... and Fastest.... Zip-lines and activities in all of Asia. We offer 6-7 hours of amazing adventure and fun... and safe for the whole family. Enjoy over 34 platforms and activity stations as you explore one of earth's most precious eco-systems high in the treetops 50m above the Rainforest floor.

title: Big Mindful Thanks to all of my classmates 4E1, 2011 Bishan Park Secondary School
tags: Bishan|park|secondary|school|class|4E1|2011|Mr|Peterson|prom|night|gift|how|to|make|key|chain|bishan park secondary school|present for classmates|graduation presents|prom night gifts|key chains for friends|DYI key chain|khmer girl|cambodian girl study abroad in singapore|bishan park|study abroad|singapore study abroad|life studying abroad
description:
In this video, I am showing you the process of me making all the key chains that are for my classmates, 4E1, 2011, as a graduation present. I also show you guys what I get from my friends as my graduation gifts as well! 

I also share with you about how in our class we have this "angel letter" system where everyone is assigned to one of the classmates. And then we are the angel guardian of that student. so SHOUTOUT TO MY ANGEL! if you are watching this video, please let me know who you are! hahaha 

On top of this video, I would like to give my greatest gratitude to Mr. Peterson who made it possible for me to give out meaningful gifts to all of my classmates, even though he had a tons of things to do on Prom Night itself. THANK YOU SO MUCH !!

I hope you will keep in touch with me. Being one of your friends means a lot to me. I love you guys.

Pole Dance Instagram: https://instagram.com/lyneth_m‚Äã

SWISS BLUE TOPAZ.

Welcome to Navneet Gems & Minerals you-tube channel.

Navneet Gems and Minerals has been manufacturing blue topaz gemstones and trading all around the world. If you are looking for wholesale supplier of Blue topaz that gives professional service, great prices directly from our factory and great quality and polished in Thailand then 
Navneet Gems is perfect space for you. 

What are Swiss Blue Topaz Gems? 
Swiss Blue Topaz is medium blue colored topaz which is lighter than London Blue and darker than sky blue topaz. We have been supplying different shapes and sizes in swiss blue topaz gemstones. You can buy every regular shape in rounds, cushions, octagons, squares, marquise, baguettes, ovals and other shapes.

Welcome to Navneet Gems' youtube channel.

Our company is 25 years in the wholesale gemstone business and our aim on our youtube channel is not only to sell gemstones.

üíé About Navneet Gems:

Navneet Gems is a manufacturer and wholesale supplier of well dimensioned, cut and polished Wholesale Precious Gemstones and Wholesale Semi Precious Gemstones along with Silver, Brass and Gold Jewelry. 

The company was founded by Mr. Suresh Agarwal in 1993 (now the major part of the business is lead by his son Navneet Agarwal) headquartered in Bangkok, Thailand  and Jaipur, India,  where we have our own Gemstone factories in both the Cutting hubs. 

Our company is involved not only in many different types of Semi Precious Gemstones (more than a 100 different types) but also our company qualifies to supply some of the most finely cut and selected Precious Gemstones from our factory. 

The only reason Precious Gemstones are not easy to source is because there are various types of qualities and color of these precious stones. The price and quality vary greatly.

title: Hiking Krabi's Tab Kak Hang Nak Nature Trail | Ngon Nak Mountain Summit
tags: hang|nak|summit|Thailand|thailand travel|vacation|travel|adventure|hiking|thailand vacation|park|nature|climbing|krabi|things to do krabi|things to do in thailand|ngorn nak|ngorn|mountain|Tab Kak Hang Nak Nature Trail|Tab Kak Hiking Krabi|Krabi Hiking|Krabi Nature Trail|Ngon Nak Hiking Trail
description:
Tab Kak Hang Nak Nature Trail Hiking in Krabi is amazing at this mountain peak trail. Great view encompassing the Ao Nang and Noppharat Thara Beaches, Thalen Bay, Krabi, Krabi Town, all over the area. 

Our Tab Kak Nature Trail PDF GUIDE - FREE - https://seekrabi.com/hang-nak-nature-trail-guide-krabi/

Anyway - this is southern Thailand, on a good day. Sunshine and white clouds... blue skies.

This mountain is amazing - a great hike and simply awesome view from the top. There is a race up it annually if you can figure out when it is. The race is every year in March.

There are not many hikes in Krabi, this is the best. There is a walk up Wat Tum Sua steps (1,256 steps) and there are a couple walks on nature trails like over at Crystal Pool (Sra Morakot).

https://SeeKrabi.com for all your Krabi, Thailand vacation needs!

title: Phuket Scuba Diving - Merlin Divers in Kamala
description:
https://phuket-diving-thailand.net/

Kamala Diving Center -- Merlin Divers -- the premier scuba dive shop in Kamala, only 50 meters from the beautiful Kamala Beach between the beaches of Patong and Bangtao Surin -- Phuket, Thailand. Merlin Divers offers the full range of scuba diving activities that are available from Phuket and maintains one of the largest equipment shops you can find on Phuket, Thailand -- displaying and selling all sorts of diving and snorkeling equipment, swimming items and general water sports gear and wear. Merlin Divers is an official dealer and partner of Aqualung scuba diving equipment for diving and snorkeling and Suunto dive computer.

title: Pattaya Dolphin World and Resort
description:
Pattaya dolphin world is located next to Phoenix Golf Course southeast of Pattaya, About 20 or a 25-minute drive. It just opened (There sign said soft opening) and only the dolphin show is ready. The cost right now is 190 Baht per person, Kids shorter than 90cm get in free. They plan to have a fishing park, ATV rides, rooms for rent, Restaurants, Games and they do have horse rides happening now. 
The dolphin show lasted about 45 minutes and was lots of fun, Kids big and small loved it.


http://www.pattayadolphin-world.com/

title: Samui rock cafe & The black roses live, shot with Panasonic hdc sd 90 in full hd.
tags: Koh Samui|samui|thailand|surat thani|vacation|Samui rock cafe|rock|cafe|bar|best bar|Thai girls|beer|pool|live|music|metal|guitar solo|covers|eric clapton|black sabbath|AC/DC|Santana|panasonic|hdc|sd|90|power director|The black roses|birthday|july|2011
description:
Edit July 2019. Samui Rock cafe has been sold a few years back and is now a crab restaurant, so don't bother looking for the place. I really miss that great place and the cool people there. Black roses are still playing on Koh Samui. I just saw them the other week when in Lamai. They played Wednesdays on Bondi restaurant in Lamai.

Here is a small video i created in power director 9.
It's from our second vacation on Koh Samui Thailand and Samui Rock Cafe is located on Chaweng Lake road across the food market.

We found this really cool bar on our last vacation and Samui Rock Cafe has a really great pooltable, nice staff and the option in the bar to choose from more than 100,000 music numbers.
Great bar and we will certainly revisit this bar when we hopefully get back to Samui next year.
Chris the owner is a really cool guy and if you have any questions about Samui, he is helpful with info.
The video is shot on his birthday 26 July and he hired a great band named The black Roses and they really did a good job.
They did different covers of Eric Clapton, Black Sabbath, AC/DC, Santana and lots more.
Rock on Chris.

It's not to hard to find in Chaweng.
It's Opposite the food market on Chaweng lake road.
If you come from the start of the northern Chaweng main road, turn down Chaweng lake road. (where Chaweng main road starts to go in one direction only, and there is a big jeweler on the corner)
Keep going down Chaweng lake road for about 200 meters or so and it's on the right side and across the food market where Mitra restaurant is located.

Best bar on the island if you ask me.

To Chris if you see this.
Thanks for a great time and we will return next year when we hopefully come back to Samui.
Would be cool if we could return on your birthday.
And hopefully i'm better at pool next year ;)
Give our regards to Jenny and your staff.
Lotte and Jimmi. 
Denmark.

title: Arthroscopic Shoulder Surgery (Thailand): Rotator Cuff | Bumrungrad Hospital
tags: arthroscopy thailand|shoulder surgery thailand|rotator cuff surgery|bumrungrad|bangkok
description:
Bumrungrad International: Video of an arthroscopic shoulder surgery in Thailand (rotator cuff repair).

This video shows highlights from the repair of two torn tendons, one partially torn tendon, torn cartilage and a torn bicep.
 
0:46 beings the cleaning of the cartilage and torn tissue.
3:04 begins the insertion of a titanium screw.
3:35 shows the insertion of the threads used to secure the tendons.
4:20 begins a demonstration of a tying of a knot used to secure the thread.

Read more: Arthroscopic Shoulder Surgery (Rotator Cuff)

title: YvW Episode 4.5: Sak Yant, Traditional Northern Thai Monastery Handpoke Magic Tattoo
tags: sak yant|magic tattoo|tu eak|thailand|tattooing|hand poke tattoo|Buddha|monk|monastery tattoo|holy tattoo|traveling tattooer|yorkatronic|decade of travel|wayfarer|tattooer|bamboo tattoo|buddhism|magic|Tu Eak
description: Humbled to be recieving my Sak Yant, the traditional hand poke tattoo in Thailand. My tattooer is Tu Eak in Chiang Mai, who at the time was considered to apply the most powerful tattoos in the country. Other monks from all over Thailand travel to be tattooed by him, as his magic is considered the strongest. I received a "success" Yant in the form of Buddha's lotus. Honestly, after the blessing at the end, I felt like i had this golden glow around me. it was a really incredible experience.

title: Lao Cooking Class in Vientiane, Laos
tags: Laos|Vientiane|food|cooking class|mok pa|papaya salad|sticky rice and mangoes|Lao Cooking Class in Vientiane|Laos Cooking Class in Vientiane|Lao Experiences|Learn how to cook Lao food|Lao culture in Vientiane
description:
To read the entire story about my Lao ooking class in Vientiane, Laos, go to https://holeinthedonut.com/2011/06/27/cooking-school-vientiane-laos/ and if you enjoyed this video, please consider subscribing to my YouTube channel.

Always on a quest to connect with the local culture of the countries I visit, in Laos I decided to take a cooking class with Lao Experiences. In a lovely garden on the banks of the Mekong River, three Lao ladies walked me through the preparation of Mok Pa, fresh fish pounded with local spices and wrapped in steamed banana leaves; vegetables roasted on skewers, whole fish crusted in salt and roasted over hot coals, two types of dipping sauces, spicy papaya salad, and sticky rice and mangoes. Not only was it a perfect way to learn about Lao culture, it was a delicious way to spend an afternoon.

description:
YvW EPISODE 5! the Fede & Yorkatron race to Ho Chi Minh part 2! from Thailand to Angkor Wat, Cambodia, then Vietnam...shit gets wild pretty fast as the funds continue to run dry, bus seats get smaller and roads get more narrow and windy! I gave half my money away to the children in Cambodia and would do it again its astonishingly impoverished...couldn't afford deodorant after Bangkok until one of the gals we teamed up with finally bought me some out of pity (or disgust), what a ride. Accompanied by this Italian super-human we manage to cover so much country by ground we both we ready for collapse.

(youTube's new audio rights have wreaked havoc on a few of my videos, so I apologize for the mess in the first 1/3rd, it caused a whole lot of work in the aftermath, but the story remains the same)

title: Feather Ball at Wat Phnom, Phnom Penh Cambodia
description:
The artistic and the team play.

The game is played according to the rules. The game is similar to the volleyball, but the ball is different and by no means touched by the hands. The artistic game is completely different. As the name implies, it has to do with the skill of the athlete and the choreography. The winner is the one who does the most difficult and controlled subterfuges with the featherball. Individuals, pairs, or teams can play the artistic game. Both games have the same goal, to keep the ball in the air without touching the ground. The featherball is kicked with the feet, the knees, the hips, the body, but never with the hands.

http://www.shuttlecock-europe.org/sport_history.php

title: Night Market Pub Street @ Siem Reap Cambodia
description:
Angkor Night Market was established in 2007 at that time there's no night market in the whole country of Cambodia. The market founders were careful not to create a tourist park, as in often case, there's no warehouse like setting instead you will find smoothly laid out huts built from natural materials and design in beautiful Khmer style. Over the years we already have 200 souvenirs shops which sells traditional Cambodian handmade products from clothing's, silk, arts, jewelries, wood and stone carvings.

http://www.angkornightmarket.com/

title: ANGKOR WAT Siam Reap Cambodia
description:
Angkor (Khmer: ·û¢·ûÑ·üí·ûÇ·ûö) is a region of Cambodia that served as the seat of the Khmer Empire, which flourished from approximately the 9th to 15th centuries. The word Angkor is derived from the Sanskrit nagara (‡§®‡§ó‡§∞), meaning "city".[1] The Angkorian period began in AD 802, when the Khmer Hindu monarch Jayavarman II declared himself a "universal monarch" and "god-king", until 1431, when Ayutthayan invaders sacked the Khmer capital, causing its population to migrate south to the area of Phnom Penh.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angkor

title: Cheap Eats - Street Food at the Night Market in Luang Prabang, Laos
tags: travel|culture|street food|Luang Prabang|Laos|night market|Street Food at the Night Market in Luang Prabang|Sisavangvong Street|night market in Luang Prabang Laos|Cheap Eats|How to eat in Luang Prabang for $3
description:
To read the entire story about street food at the night market in Luang Prabang, Laos, go to https://holeinthedonut.com/2011/05/27/sucker-for-street-food/, and if you enjoyed this video, please consider subscribing to my YouTube channel.

Every evening in Luang Prabang, Sisavangvong Street is closed down to traffic and becomes a pedestrian mall where visitors can buy local handicrafts ranging from purses to sequined wall hangings to traditional Lao scarves. But the very best part of the market are the street food vendors tucked into a narrow alley at the end of the market. Tables covered with hundreds of silver bowls containing Lao delicacies stretch for blocks and women do their best to rope customers in with promises of "all you can eat buffets." It's easy to eat here for less than three dollars, and everything I ever tried was delicious.

title: Night Market Phnom Penh Cambodia
description:
Phnom Penh: the name can't help but conjure up an image of the exotic. The glimmering spires of the royal palace, the fluttering saffron of the monks' robes, and the luscious location on the banks of the mighty Mekong; this is one of Asia's undiscovered gems. But it's also a city on the move, as a new wave of investors move in, perhaps forever changing the character, and skyline, of this classic city. Phnom Penh is a crossroads of Asia's past and present, a city of extremes of poverty and excess, of charm and chaos, but one that never fails to captivate.

http://www.lonelyplanet.com/cambodia/phnom-penh

2011

title: Angkor Wat Siam Reap Cambodia - Watching the sunrise
description:
Sunrise Over Angkor Wat

Watching the sunrise over Angkor Wat is a virtual pre-requisite of any visit to Siem Reap and the Angkor temple complex nearby and mine was no different. It was my first full day of exploration on this trip and my guide, Soydy, was waiting for me outside the hotel doors early at 4.30am. Navigating my way around the sleeping front desk clerk and his hammock strung across the stairway, I climbed aboard Soydy's moto and we were off. The streets were already alive with people despite the early hour and the darkness, although their shapes were a blur and only highlighted by the beam of our motorbike lights. We drove past the recently refurbished Grand d'Angkor hotel and out along the seven kilometre road to the temples. The cool breeze helped to wake me up as we slowed to a halt at the main ticket booth. Soydy had given me my temple pass when he picked me up and by torchlight, my ticket was inspected, stamped and signed. We carried on, speeding past a procession of locals making their way into the temple complex by bicycle.

http://www.btinternet.com/~andy.brouwer/sunrise.htm

2011

title: Siem Reap Cambodia - Pub Street at night
tags: Pub Street or Bar Street|Pub Street|foods|night market|Cambodia|Siem Reap|Angkor Thom|Angkor Wat|Sunset|Sunrise üåÑ
description:
The growth of the area started on what is now almost officially (there's a sign up now) known as "Pub Street" or "Bar Street," depending on your choice of terminology, but food and drink options have since spread to a number of surrounding streets as well.

"Pub Street" itself would at this point, probably be more accurately known as "Food Street". With two exceptions, The Angkor What? Bar and the Temple Club, as the emphasis here is now almost entirely on food opposed to drinking. That said, in the alleys and streets running both parallel and perpendicular to "Pub/Bar/Food Street" you can not only find more restaurants but many bars as well. Drinking until the wee hours of the morning remains a very viable activity here. The alleyway to the north of "Pub Street" has recently seen several new bars open, while the alleyway to the south has been filled up with restaurants. 

http://www.talesofasia.com/cambodia-siemreap-guide-eat.htm

title: The Killing Fields @ Choeung EK, Phnom Penh Cambodia
description:
The Killing Fields are a number of sites in Cambodia where large numbers of people were killed and buried by the Khmer Rouge regime, during its rule of the country from 1975 to 1979, immediately after the end of the Vietnam War.

The best known monument of the Killing Fields is Choeung Ek.

title: International Samui Bike Week 2011
tags: Koh Samui AT CHAWENG LAKE|KOH SAMUI|thailand|motorbike|engine|bangkok|Samui Bike Week 2011|cycling|Ko Samui (Island)|Outdoor Sports|Bike|Ride|Bicycle|Riding|Riders|festival|Biking|Khmer|Trial|Trail|Dirt|Fest
description:
AT CHAWENG LAKE, KOH SAMUI, THAILAND

"Samui - The Green Island and The Blue Ocean"
Samui Rider Club welcomes all bikers who love riding to come to International Samui Bike Week 2011 festival. In this festival, there are many bikers' clubs, all big bike brand and including The Haley-Devidson coming to the show. We would like to invite both Thais and Foreigners who are interested in the two wheels.
There were more than a thousand riders participated last year. For this year, we try harder to provide for more participants enjoying their time during the week. There are varieties of concert bands, many shops, selected famous local food stands and a cowboy's show. On top of these, you will be able to join bikers' activities and amaze with various fabulous motorbikes' brand presenting.
Moreover, this festival is a part of social responsible project, which is "The Riding for Peace and Environment". The aim is to gathering loving riders to show their power, spirit and unity. This is for riding together peacefully among different people and different nation. Then after the festival, we will donate some parts of the income to The Green Island Project for sustainable conveniences and promoting the greening our Koh Samui, greening our world.
Last but not least, Samui Riders' Club would like to thank our sponsors and supporters including Koh Samui Municipality, Tourism Association of Koh Samui, and Koh Samui -- Tourism Authority of Thailand very much for all

description: Made by The Commonwealth Film Unit 1966. Directed by John Abbott. In making this film about the Vietnam War, the Australian Commonwealth Film Unit did not look for battles and heroes. This was to be the story of the young Australians who were carrying on the standards of service begun by their grandfathers during the First World War. The emphasis was on people, both Australian and Vietnamese. The intention was to show what war really feels like.

description:

HERE IS ONE MORE MY VIDEO ABOUT STREET FOOD Ihttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rr6SSVoZi-w Village Food Factory Asia

Serious Sausages in Chiang Mai
by Allan Wilson
I can‚Äôt say I‚Äôve eaten through every sai oua sausage (Chiang Mai Sausage / Northern Thai Sausage). In fact it is rare that I even call into the city at all. But I do know my sausage. So I will go out on a limb and say that some of the best Sai Oua Northern Thai sausage in Chiang Mai is found at the Mae Hia Fresh Market, aka Talad Sod Mae Hai. It‚Äôs all very subjective, I know, but going by local recommendation, the lines of queues to reach them, and just the sheer number they grill up on a daily basis, it‚Äôs just really hard to find something similar in Chiang Mai.

Mae Hia Fresh Market
For those looking for it, the stall at Mae Hia Market, or mini kitchen as it may be better described, is called Gao Makham (which translates as under the tamarind tree). But it isn‚Äôt written in English so this is fairly useless to most. To find it just look for the long queues in the near corner of the market (by the road) and, from there, it is honestly hard to miss. There are grills upon grills of sai oua Northern Thai sausage. Sausage so fresh, and so crumbly, that it falls apart when you poke it with a stick.




Street food in Thailand. My dinner today 1 / Thai sausage - Sai Grok

Thai cuisine is the national cuisine of Thailand. Blending elements of several Southeast Asian traditions, Thai cooking places emphasis on lightly prepared dishes with strong aromatic components. The spiciness of Thai cuisine is well known. As with other Asian cuisines, balance, detail and variety are of great significance to Thai chefs. Thai food is known for its balance of three to four fundamental taste senses in each dish or the overall meal: sour, sweet, salty, and bitter.
As an acknowledged expert of Thai cuisine, David Thompson, explains in an interview: "Thai food ain't about simplicity. It's about the juggling of disparate elements to create a harmonious finish. Like a complex musical chord it's got to have a smooth surface but it doesn't matter what's happening underneath. Simplicity isn't the dictum here, at all. Some westerners think it's a jumble of flavours, but to a Thai that's important, it's the complexity they delight in.

P.S. for those who see here anal beads - rest in peace

Gao Makham
I actually find that unlike hawker stalls of Singapore and maybe Malaysia, that Thai people aren‚Äôt too fond of waiting in queues. Or at least when they‚Äôre not comfortable, and when not sat inside air-conditioned malls. But to find Gao Makham it is important to look for the queues, because there is a very similar sai oua sausage stall on the opposite corner of Mae Hia Market. This second shop is called Sai oua samonprai (which translates as herbal sausage) and it is quite possibly the second best sai oua Northern Thailand sausage in Chiang Mai.

What is bangkok's atmosphere like? It is a real Bangkok!:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EvDBAs-a228 Where is Best Pad Thai in Thailand?

title: Stampede in cambodia 2010
tags: MVI|1653|stameped|viral video|cambodia waterfestival|2010|Khmer|Koh pich island|Diamond island
description:
"Original video footage"
The Cambodian every year celebrates the 3 days of Water Festival 20th 21st and 22nd of November in Phnom Pehn City...this year 2010, they expected thousands of people coming or celebrating the event..alots of entertainment, live cambodian band music, a huge fireworks, boat racing in the mekong river, and alots of stuff to buy with great discounts..ive been celebrating the water festival for three times, this time me, myself is there walking at the diamond island through the bridge not knowing that stampede will happen..at first the flow of the crowd is well organise and so on, after that when ive reached to the center of the bridge the crowd stop flowing and then suddenly somebody shouts.maybe like " move forward" the others "move backward" then people pushing each from my side and to the other end side of the bridge they keep pushing and pushing,some they do elbow and i was heat at that time they step on my feet..then i was thinking its gonna be a stampede..after that ive reached to the nearest metal of the bridge. when i look behind its still very far and alot of people stuck and i cant move forward and backward already, so i had to climb up and jump off the bridge but not into the water that was the first stage of stampede..and after that my hands and feet are shaking and yet still taking pictures and video at that time.. thanks to the LORD JESUS CHRIST, MOTHER MARY, SNR. SAN ROQUE, SNR. SANTO NINO, AND SANTO THOMAS DE VILLANEUVA..theyve heard my prayers and lead the way to escape from the stamped.. thank you for the second chance and a second LIFE oh praise the LORD JESUS CHRIST...

title: Snake Temple, Penang, Malaysia
tags: Penang|Malaysia|snake temple|pit vipers Chinese|Taoist|Snake Temple in Penang Malaysia|Taoist Chinese temple|Buddhist monk named Chor Soo Kong
description:
To read the entire story about my visit to the Snake Temple in Penang, Malaysia, go to https://holeinthedonut.com/2010/10/04/snake-temple-penang-malaysia/, and if you enjoyed this video, please consider subscribing to my YouTube channel.

This Taoist Chinese temple on the southern end of the island in Penang, Malaysia, may be the only one of its kind in the world. It was built in 1850 to venerate Buddhist monk named Chor Soo Kong. Soon after completion pit viper snakes from the surrounding untouched jungle began making their way into the temple. Rather than clean them out, monks welcomed the snakes and became their protectors. Today much of the land around the temple has been developed into factories, thus the number of snakes is much reduced, but dozens still arrive each day and drape themselves in potted plants and wooden "tree stands" that are set upon the altars. Though poisonous, it is believed that incense from burning joss sticks has rendered the snakes harmless. Even so, signs abound, warning visitors not to handle the poisonous serpents, as they lie out in the open with no cages or other barriers to separate them from worshipers.

This basic scuba diving skill is required, either in the PADI Instructor Development Courses (IDC), the PADI Divemaster course and in the Open Water Diver course. This demonstration is presented by PADI Instructor / Course Director Alain Cacao Barrat. He is based and teaches PADI scuba diving courses in French and in English on Phuket. Island located in Thailand. 
https://oxybullesdiving.com/ and
https://alain-phuket-idc.wixsite.com/oxybullesasiapacific/home
Here below are the critical attributes to demonstrate and to teach the Skill in French and in English.

Attributs critiques:
‚Ä¢ En eaux profondes.
‚Ä¢ Placez une ligne de r√©f√©rence de 7,5 m. Ensuite, placez les √©tudiants au milieu en face de celle-ci.
‚Ä¢ Placez-vous √† l'une des extr√©mit√©s.
‚Ä¢ D√©montrer le signe de la comp√©tence.
‚Ä¢ D√©montrez que de l'air doit √™tre ajout√© dans le gilet stabilisateur tout en prenant une position horizontale.
‚Ä¢ Restez dans cette position.
‚Ä¢ Montrez toutes les √©tapes pour retirer le masque et maintenez-le.
‚Ä¢ Utilisez la ligne comme r√©f√©rence tactile, en nageant sur les premiers 7.5 m√®tres.
‚Ä¢ Une fois arriv√© √† l'autre extr√©mit√©, orientez, replacez et purgez le masque.
(Rappelez-vous que la personne qui fait la d√©monstration, elle n'a pas besoin de parcourir toute la distance des 15 m√®tres. Elle doit souligner toutes les √©tapes, afin de faciliter la pratique de l‚Äô√©l√®ve plongeur)

Critical Attributes:
‚Ä¢ In deep water.
‚Ä¢ Place a reference line of 7.5m. Then place the students in the middle facing it.
‚Ä¢ Position yourself at one end of the line.
‚Ä¢ Demonstrate the skill's signal.
‚Ä¢ Demonstrate that air must be added in the BCD while taking a horizontal position.
‚Ä¢ Stay in this position.
‚Ä¢ Demonstrate all steps to remove the mask and hold it.
‚Ä¢ Use the line as a tactile reference, swim the first 7.5 meters.
‚Ä¢ Once arrived to the other end, orientate, replace and clear the mask.
(Remember that the person doing the Demo, she doesn't have to swim the full distance of 15 meters. She needs to emphasize all the different steps, in order to facilitate the student diver's practice)

tags: krabi|krabi town|ao|nang|ao nang|thailand krabi|Krabi Thailand|krabi beaches|ao nang krabi|southern|thailand|things to do krabi|krabi activities|thai|krabong|outdoors|nature|krabi province|krabi attractions|southern thailand|slideshow
description:
Things to do in Krabi, Thailand. Temples, natural tourist attractions, hikes up mountains, etc. Photo collection of Krabi. 

Our Krabi site: https://SeeKrabi.com

Personally, I think that Krabi province in Southern Thailand has more to do than any other province in the country, except maybe Phuket - which is a tie. Phuket has the nightlife and Krabi has the peace of mind, the abundance of natural wilderness exploration locations, national parks, and laid back atmosphere.

If you are considering moving to Thailand to live you should check out all parts of the country and decide which is the better place to retire to - or you can stay a couple years in the northeast, couple years in the north, couple in Bangkok, couple in the islands, couple in the south - and do it all again.

Our site: https://SeeKrabi.com
