title: KEBESARAN ALLAH
tags: KEBESARAN|ALLAH|surah|yaasin|pasir|mas|seberang|al|fatihah|kaabah|nabi|muhammad|kelantan|klate|malaysia|kuasa|god|power|kota bharu|rtm|tv3|astro|noranectv|neelofa|ajaib|yassin|doa|prayers|pray|vivy|duck|viral|motif viral|sejarah|tempat|bersejarah|unik|merdeka|rasul|rasulullah|ectv|noran|swt|islam|islamic|muslim|zakir naik|zakir|uai|ustaz azhar idrus|azhar idrus|mecca|mekah|madinah|tengku nik aziz|ya allah|subhanallah|alhamdulillah|ebit|lew
description:
Bila kita teliti ketika membaca surah "yaasin" pada ayat ke 82 bertemulah kita dengan kalimat "kun fayakun", iaitu perintah Allah SWT terhadap sesuatu cukuplah dengan kalimat : "Jadilah, maka terjadilah".
Begitu juga dengan kejadian yang berlaku di Kampung Seberang Pasir Mas, Salor yang dulunya terkenal kesibukan kenderaan untuk menyeberangi sungai melalui feri.
Rimbunan pokok menarik perhatian ramai dan saya sempat merakamkan kejadian aneh ini kelmarin 15 Syaaban sempena dgn fadhilat pahala sesiapa membaca 3 kali Surah Yaasin dgn niat dia akan dipanjangkan umur diberkati rezeki yang halal dan akan ditetapkan iman sehingga kesaat akhir.
Anda buat tafsiran sendiri dengan kejadian ini, saya cuma nampak pada zahirnya sahaja.
Saya gabungkan juga visual ini dengan kejadian awan membentuk seperti kaabah, ketika umat Islam sibuk mengerjakan haji di Mekah.
Maka sempurnalah visual ini untuk anda tonton dengan kejadian yang sama berlaku di kampung kelahiran saya.
Menariknya objek ini menghala ke kiblat seolah olah sedang solat atau membaca al-quran dengan khusuknya.
Perhatikan betul2 bentuk rupanya ada mata, hidung, mulut dan janggut sejemput.... bye.. hope ada komen walaupun sepatah. Tq.

title: American Nurse Appreciates Professionalism at Dental Implant Center #BIDC 2
description:
Patient review by American nurse, a healthcare provider in USA on having her extensive dental treatment at BIDC dental implant center that included re-treatment of root canal treatment teeth extractions, deep cleaning and 3 dental implants.
 

‚ÄúClinic: What treatments did you do here?
Nurse: I had quite a bit done. I had a long history of dental problems And since coming here, I had an initial consultation Then I had a root canal redone that was quite infected I also had three fillings done I had four teeth pulled I had three dental implants put in I also had a bone grafting done I also had a deep root cleaning as well and now I'm just about finished It started in October. I had a couple of appointments in October and then the work couldn't be completed because there had to be a healing process so then I came back in January all at convenient times for me which I really appreciate There was never any question. It was always to see that whenever I could come, they could do it

Clinic: What is your general impression about the dentist or the clinic?
Nurse: Well, I'm a healthcare professional myself. So I can really appreciate the professionalism of everyone The promise of the appointment The fact that if something goes not as expected, the dentist will come in on their time-off to correct the problem I think the fact that you can move through the clinic, clearly without any long waiting periods It just seem to run very smoothly and efficiently At the same time compassionately and professionally And as a healthcare professional I appreciate that.

Clinic: Thank you very much
Nurse: You're very welcome. My pleasure‚Äù

title: Elephant Paints A Picture in Thailand
description:
http://www.TravelsWithSheila.com
The best part of the Chiang Dao Elephant Camp performance was when a baby elephant actually painted a picture stroke by stroke. The elephant would daintily take the paintbrush from its mahout and paint. Mahout then changed paintbrush colors and elephant would paint some more.

The most incredible part is the elephant painted a tree, grass and flowers. So smart!

title: The Chiang Dao Elephant Camp, Thailand
description:
http://www.TravelsWithSheila.com
There are many elephant camps in Thailand. Some funded and run by the Thai Government while others are private. The Chiang Dao Elephant Camp is privately run and only about an hour's ride north of Chiang Mai.

There is an admission fee that entitles you to watch Elephant Bathing and an Elephant Performance. I am now enlightened (11 years after this visit,) and can only think...Elephant abuse! Read the latest National Geographic for more on this subject...

description:
Thai Food Cooking Vlog - LAAB GAI (Chicken in spicy sour salad) | JoysThaiFood

Laab Gai (lab gai or gy) Gai means chicken. Laab is the kind of spicy and sour dish this is. This is one of our - and Thailand's favorite recipes ever... You must try it out if you really like spicy hot food. This is one of my husband's favorite Thai dishes! :)

It contains chicken, onions, parsley, Thai crushed rice, garlic, spicy chilis, Thai basil (grapow), and other spices and ingredients.

title: Hiking Krabi Thailand | Hang Nak Nature Trail in Tab Kak (Tub Kaek) Krabi by Ao Nang Beach in Krabi
tags: hiking thailand|in krabi trekking krabi|thiland|tailand|thailand travel|thailand|tourist|outdoors|wildlife|hiking|outdoor|educational|cool|nature|travel log|ngorn nak|Hang Nak Nature Trail|Tab Kak Hang Nak Nature Trail Krabi|Krabi Hiking|Krabi Nature Trail|Ao Nang Hiking|Krabi Things to Do
description:
Hang Nak Mountain Trail also known as Ngorn Nak Nature Trail and crested dragon trail is an amazing mountain peak with 360-degree views of the beach and surrounding limestone karsts. Excellent hike as you trek 500 meters vertical height above sea level. One of the Top Things to Do in Krabi, Thailand. Thiland. Tiland.

Update - I've been up this mountain around 450 times now. It's a great hike, few snakes, always some lizards, sometimes a water monitor... There isn't much hiking in Krabi - but this is the ultimate place to go for it. STAY ON THE TRAIL... it is easy to get lost, and it's a very large area to get lost in. I've helped numerous people to get off the mountain when lost. Sometimes they were lost until after midnight. Not fun. lol...

Grab my FREE GUIDE to Hang Nak Nature Trail on PDF here - https://seekrabi.com/hang-nak-nature-trail-guide-krabi/

 Long-tail Boat - The engine is invariably mounted on an inboard turret-like pole which can rotate through 180 degrees, allowing steering by thrust vectoring. The propeller is mounted directly on the driveshaft with no additional gearing or transmission. Usually the engine also swivels up and down to provide a "neutral gear" where the propeller does not contact the water. The driveshaft must be extended by several metres of metal rod to properly position the propeller, giving the boat its name and distinct appearance.

title: The Wonderful People of Vietnam
description:
http://www.TravelsWithSheila.com
It's difficult to fathom the misery the Vietnam people have suffered for many years.  Wars, oppression, forces of nature...and through it all, they extend such a warm welcome with beautiful smiles to everyone.

It is this that had us returning to Vietnam for a third time.  A diversity of weather, food, minorities, historic sites...so very much to see.  Visit, if you haven't already and prepare for a wonderful experience.

title: N.W. Vietnam:  A Sapa Day Trek
description:
http://www.TravelsWithSheila.com
All Sapa tour operators can arrange single day treks or multiple day treks with homestays along the way.  Our hotel, The Royal Hotel Sapa, was loaded with tourists heading out to visit the villages.  Some had just arrived on the morning train from Hanoi.

Any trek you take is not a solitary experience.  You will accompanied by hundreds of other tourists while the Black Hmong use all their persuasive powers to sell you something...anything...

title: Mandarin Oriental @ Chiang Mai Thailand
description:
Mandarin Oriental @ Chiang Mai
Hotel Review posted by Mathieu, Belgium in June 2005 
This hotel is a work of art.  When we heard the owner spent over 100 million euro to build it, we felt every penny was well spent!  We stayed at the deluxe villa with a jacuzzi, which was spacious and luxurious (over 200 square meters of space), but watch out for the mosquitos at night.  There was a DVD player in the room plus the hotel has a DVD library from which you can borrow films.

The feeling created is one of a traditional village, so you really feel you're at home. Every morning and night when we came back to our villa, a guard greeted us at the street corner.  We especially loved having breakfast on the terrace looking out to the rice paddy fields, and although it's a bit pricey (20 euro as I recall) and not included in the rate, it's a must!  The complimentary yoga and pilates classes made the stay more "healthy". We also recommend hiring the hotel limousine for airport pick up and drop-off service. For a mere 20 euro per trip, you feel like royalty.  Since we stayed at the hotel during the soft opening, some of the facilities weren't yet ready (not a problem though---didn't miss out). We cannot wait to go back when everything is complete.  And there were also 2 computers with Internet connection free of charge. We HIGHLY recommend this place. It's expensive but it's worth it. We loved it!
 
http://www.asiarooms.com/thailand/chiang_mai/mandarin_oriental_dhara_dhevi-hotel-reviews/103763.html

title: Langkawi Island Malaysia Dusky Leaf Langgur newborn baby
description:
Our chief found this baby langur mourning the dead mother on the side of the road. her family members were not around anymore. we took it to Ima to look after and the baby has now adopted Ima as its mother. Its a female baby and we hope she survive and can return  to the wild. Thanks all for viewing and please pray all the best for her.

About JungleWalla.
JungleWalla was formed in 1994 is the pioneer of nature tourism in Langkawi and adheres to ecological best practices standards. With the truly extensive range of signature tours available, you will have no difficulty finding a program that matches your interest and fitness level. Catering to families with kids, children enjoy preferential rates. 

To minimize the impact on environment and wildlife, and to ensure a personalized guest experience, the number of participants per tour is limited. Early bookings are therefore highly recommended.

Ketua kami menjumpai bayi langur ini meratapi ibunya yang mati di tepi jalan. Ahli keluarganya sudah tidak ada lagi. Kami membawanya kepada Ima untuk menjaganya dan bayi itu telah menganggap Ima sebagai ibunya. Ini adalah bayi betina dan kami harap dia dapat bertahan dan dapat kembali ke alam liar. Terima kasih semua kerana melihat dan doakan yang terbaik untuknya.

title: Penang Island Malaysia - Pearl of the Orient
description:
Penang Island Malaysia
Also known as the "Pearl of the Orient"

Pearl of the Orient 
By Choong Kwee Kim

Food, the beach, more food, more stretches of golden sand -- that's what the Pearl of the Orient has become famous for and still is. Penang, comprising a tropical island and mainland Province Wellesley (or Seberang Prai) in the north-west of Peninsular Malaysia, is a former Straits Settlement that still exudes an old world charm in the inner city of George Town. 

Old world charm 

The narrow streets of old George Town are flanked by pre-war houses that feature interesting architectural remnants of the past. The Malay community centred around the 
Acheen Street mosque and Kapitan Keling Mosque area, thrive in close proximity to the Chinatown areas of Campbell Street, Kimberly Street and Carnarvon Street. A totally different experience is in store a few streets away where colourful sarees, the smell of exotic spices and loud radio broadcasts of Indian songs characterise the Little India enclave. 
Apart from heritage, tourism is another strong point of Penang with its hawker food and beaches among its assets. 

Hawker food central 

The famous Penang laksa, rojak, char koay teow, nasi kandar, pasembur, chendol and muar chee are among the cheap and delicious local dishes that attract food lovers from far and near to savour them at roadside stalls. 
Along the Batu Feringghi tourism belt are hotels, resorts and service apartments that generate a lively atmosphere full of touristy goings-on. The sun and surf on the north of the idyllic island is contrasted with the factories at the industrial zone on the south-eastern tip that contribute significantly to the state's revenue. 

Northern industrial zone 

Many multinational corporations have their bases here and provide employment opportunities to locals, precipitating the growth of new townships in the suburban areas outside of the state capital. 
Penang, despite being a small state that is home to a population of only 1.3 million, is a thriving place that offers an interesting blend of the old and new. 

The Star Online Malaysia (http://www.thestar.com.my)

title: Vietnam Motorcycle Tours, Enduro Tours of Northwest Vietnam | VietnamOffroad.Com
tags: Vietnam Motorcycle Tours|Vietnam Motorbike Tours|Hanoi Motorcycle Tours|Motorbike Tours Vietnam|Motorcycle Tours Vietnam|Vietnam Motorcycle Holidays|Motorbike Hire Vietnam|northwest vietnam motorbike tour|northwest vietnam motorcycle tour|northwest vietnam dirt bike tour|northwest vietnam scooter tour|north-west vietnam motorbike tour|north-west vietnam motorcycle tour|north-west vietnam dirt bike tour|north-west vietnam scooter tour|vietnam enduro tours|northwest
description:
Vietnam Off-road Motorbike Tours (https://vietnamoffroad.com) offers professional Northwest Vietnam dirt bike or enduro tours from Hanoi, Vietnam. This video is about a ride in Northwest Vietnam back in 2007. Sorry for the quality of this video, in 2007 we didn't have much choice :)

Northwest Vietnam is one of the best areas for motorcycling in Northern Vietnam. It's home to about 30 different groups of hill tribes. Currently, a hydro-electric plant has been built in Muong Lay and the roads are not so good before and after Muong Lay. Northwest Vietnam used to be a far and difficult part of Vietnam. It‚Äôs more famous for the war against the French Army in Dien Bien Phu. It now turns into a major tourist attraction that grabs attention from old to young people. Some travel there to see the former battlefield of Dien Bien Phu while more people choose to ride on a motorcycle tour to take in the breathtaking views and conquer the high mountain passes. More roads are being built, but there are still many areas that can only be accessible by motorbikes. You start from Hanoi, head up the mountains on the historical Highway 6 and snake up and down the rig zag mountain roads, meet colorful hill tribe groups, and visit their weekend markets. Places you see include Mai Chau, Phu Yen, Moc Chau, Son La, Tuan Giao, Muong Lay, Sin Ho, Dien Bien Phu, Sapa, Bac Ha, Luc Yen, and Vu Linh. There are homestays in Mai Chau, Sapa, Bac Ha, Luc Yen, and Vu Linh. In other places, we use hotels that offer better facilities. A mix of homestays and hotels is great and you will have many good things to tell your friend after this ride. Allow at least 7 days to have a good loop, please let us know your expectation and we will tailor-make an itinerary together.

Don't take our words about how great and trustworthy we are, just check at https://vietnamoffroad.com/testimonials (no fake reviews, all real, both positive and some negative) and see what our customers said. Nobody is perfect so we posted comments "as is", no lie and no hide. This is very important to decide who to ride with in Vietnam.

tags: Thai|food|market|thailand|foods|thaifood|tai|ty|markets|Thai market|thai food|thailand food|bangkok food|bangkok|asia|asia market|food market|Thai Night Market|Thai food market|Thailand food market|Thailand street market|Thai food street market|Joys Thai Food|Thailand snacks|Thailand meals|Night Market Surat Thani
description:
See a walk-thru of a Thai food Market in Thailand! 

Here, we walk through a night market with a variety of Thai foods to make your mouth water! There are many snack foods like pork balls on a stick because many Thais don't want to eat healthy, they just want something that fills them up. So, they might have a piece of fried chicken and ball of sticky rice, or something like that just to make them full. Som tam and sticky rice works too! As does som tam and mango dessert! Getting hungry here...

Stop by my Thai food blog when you can, it's "Joy's Thai Food" at https://JoysThaiFood.com for authentic Thailand recipes I make at home.

title: Thai Recipe - Som Tam (Papaya Salad) at Night Market in Thailand | JoysThaiFood
tags: som|tam|tum|night|market|somtam|somtum|Thai|Thailand|food|salad|foods|recipe|recipes|cooking|cook|video|videos|thai food|howto|thailand travel|thai foods|som tam salad thailand|Thai favorites|Thailand favorite food|making som tam|Thai food recipes|Thai food cooking|SOM TAM INGREDIENTS
description:
Thai Recipe - Som Tam (Papaya Salad) at Night Market in Thailand | JoysThaiFood

Making Som Tam at a night market close to where we live in southern Thailand. This is a Thai woman mixing up the ingredients for som tam at outdoor night market in Surat Thani, Thailand. Som tum is the favorite food of the entire nation of Thailand!

I think most Thai people eat som tam at least once per week, but most of us like to have it at least 3-5 times per week. Some people cannot go an entire day without eating som tam!

Som tam has many different ingredients depending on the style of som tam. Usually - unripe shaved papaya, carrot shavings, tomatoes, palm sugar, fish oil, bla-rah (fermented crap or fish paste), green beans, tiny shrimp, and garlic. I don't think I forgot anything. 

Sometimes Thais make som tam at home, but usually we just go to our local market or som tam street vendor and buy it there because we have a certain taste we like and if we know we can get it down the street for just 30 Thai Baht, it is easier to do that than making som tam on our own!
